# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Cairn .gitattributes — Line ending normalization (E1-T6)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WHY: Enforces consistent line endings across Windows/macOS/Linux.
# Without this, Windows devs commit CRLF and break shell scripts
# in Docker (Linux) and CI (Linux). `text=auto` normalizes to LF
# in the repo, checks out native line endings on each OS.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Default: auto-detect text files and normalize to LF in repo
* text=auto

# WHY: Shell scripts must always be LF — CRLF breaks #!/bin/bash
# interpretation on Linux (Docker, CI).
*.sh text eol=lf
mvnw text eol=lf

# WHY: Batch files are Windows-only, CRLF is correct.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf

# WHY: Binary files must never be diff'd or line-ending converted.
*.jar binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
